The parameters of the supraparticle porous structures, such as the surface area, porous size distribution and pore volume were analyzed via N2 ad(de)sorption isotherms (Fig. 5
                        ) and summarized in Table 2
                        . According to the IUPAC classification [64], the isotherm of the TS-1 sample is close to the type I, peculiar for microporous samples. The isotherms of the supraparticles relate to type IV with the hysteresis loop of H4 type for the “glued” sample SP-1 and of H1 type at very high p/p0 for all other supraparticles (SP-2 to 4).

